    "Figure 27 aims to classify the minimum dice coefficient value, the maximum dice coefficient value, and the average value of the minimum and maximum dice coefficients of commonly used datasets.",
    "In comparison to other datasets, ETIS-Larib DB displays the lowest dice coefficient of 39.97%, while CVC Clinic DB displays the highest dice coefficient of 99.6%.",
    "However, CVC Clinic DB displays the best results with an average dice coefficient of 83.36% compared to the other datasets.",
    "According to all datasets, hybrid ResUnet++ models with conditional random field (CRF) and test time augmentation (TTA) performed poorly with fewer dice coefficients, whereas SegNet-VGG and Faster RCNN performed best with maximum dice coefficients.",
